  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While embezzlement is a serious breach of fiduciary duty, the theft of $25,000, combined with the fact that the defendant has already made efforts toward restitution and possesses no prior criminal history, supports a rehabilitative approach over long-term incarceration. A short custodial period serves as a deterrent while accounting for the mitigating factor of partial restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
